      %h3.title
        .span Call for Papers
    :markdown
      1. The 10th Hack In Taiwan Conference ( HITCON ) will be held on 19th~22nd of August, 2014. To commemorate the 10th anniversary of the Hacks in Taiwan Conference, HITCON will be expanded into two events:
        - HITCON X Enterprise held on 19th and 20th of August at the Sheraton Grande Taipei Hotel.Since an all round hacker should not focus on techniques alone, this event will therefore focus more on topics such as information security policy, trends in information security industry, cultivation of information security professionals, and exchange between enterprises. HITCON Enterprise will provide the highest quality agenda and venue to facilitate exchange between everyone, including government agencies, civilian organizations, lecturers, audience and enterprises. This event will be similar to BlackHat.
        - HITCON X Playground held on 21st and 22nd of August at the Humanities and Social Sciences Building of Academia Sinica. We've always hoped for a DEFCON-like event in Taiwan. The word "Playground" signifies that this event will be the carnival for hackers, information security professionals and everyone from the information security community. In this event, we'll focus not only on hacking techniques, but also a variety of hacking related activities for the participants, including the HITCON CTF competition, hacker's life experience sharing talk, and other lightning talk by participants. We hope that the HITCON Playground will be a fun and peculiar event. Also, we'll lower the bar ( as in price ) to this event, so that everyone in the information security community, including students will be able to afford to join this event and social with everyone. We're planning for more interesting activities for HITCON Playground, so stay tuned to our announcements.
      2. In order to raise the awareness of information security and to cultivate the information security professionals in Taiwan, we'll be expanding the scale of this year's call for paper, the topics include information security technologies and techniques, internet surveillance, mobile devices security, threat intelligence analysis, mobile phone apps security, remote controlled device security, information security defense strategy and management, cloud security, information security events management and response, malware analysis, information security event detection and preventive measures for critical infrastructures, laws and policies regarding information security, cultivation of information security professionals, and any other related researches. We welcome everyone to submit their paper. The speaking format is 50 minutes of presentation, and is preferably technical.
      3. The call for paper of HITCON Enterprise and Playground will be held together, we welcome all the elite hackers, researchers, and friends to submit their paper at our CFP website ([http://cfp2014.hitcon.org](http://cfp2014.hitcon.org)), and select the event that they wish to submit to.
      4. For those wishing to submit their paper, please apply for an account at [http://cfp2014.hitcon.org](http://cfp2014.hitcon.org) then upload the paper there for review before 5th Jul 2014. Papers are reviewed continuously on a first come first serve basis, therefore it is recommended that the papers be submitted as early as possible. We reserve the right to end call for paper earlier if all slots are filled.
      5. For details on the speakers' honorarium and compensation, please refer to the terms and conditions on the CFP website.
      6. The HITCON committee is responsible for the non-disclosure of all CFP entries, the contents will not be disclosed without the author's consent.
      7. In addition to the above mentioned call for papers, this year's HITCON will feature a 0-day exploit demonstration. To apply, please email an unpatched and unpublished proof of concept for an exploit that you've discovered personally to agenda2014 [at] hitcon.org before 5th Jul 2014. Upon confirmation, you'll have the chance to obtain a free pass to this year's HITCON (both HITCON X Enterprise and Playground), and demonstrate the exploit on stage. All rights regarding the exploit remains with the author.

